#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "`shutdown` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:204
msgid ""
"The `shutdown` command allows you to **electronically shut down** a Linux "
"server, either immediately or after a certain period of time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "shutdown [-h] [-r] time [message]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:210
msgid ""
"Specify the shutdown time in the format `hh:mm` for a precise time, or `+mm` "
"for a delay in minutes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:212
msgid ""
"To force an immediate stop, use the word `now` in place of the time. In this "
"case, the optional message is not sent to other users of the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:214
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:318
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:720
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:1399
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[root]# shutdown -h 0:30 \"Server shutdown at 0:30\"\n"
"[root]# shutdown -r +5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:221
msgid "Options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Options | Remarks                          |\n"
"| ------- | -------------------------------- |\n"
"| `-h`    | Shuts down the system electronically. |\n"
"| `-r`    | Restarts the system.              |\n"
msgstr ""

