"| ------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| `-w`    | Writes the current history to the history file.                                                |\n"
"| `-c`    | Deletes the history of the current session (but not the contents of the `.bash_history` file). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:247
msgid "Manipulating history:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:249
msgid ""
"To manipulate the history, the following commands entered from the command "
"prompt will:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Keys               | Function                                                  |\n"
"| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| <kdb>!!</kdb>      | Recalls the last command placed.                           |\n"
"| <kdb>!n</kdb>      | Recalls the command by its number in the list.             |\n"
"| <kdb>!string</kdb> | Recalls the most recent command beginning with the string. |\n"
"| <kdb>â</kdb>       | Navigates through your history working backward in time from the most recent command. |\n"
"| <kdb>â</kdb>       | Navigates through your history working forward in time. |\n"
msgstr ""

